<HL>
   Technology Brief -- International Business Machines:
   Company to Offer Rebates
   And Free Software Packages
</HL>
<DATE>
09/05/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6
</SO>
<CO>
   IBM
</CO>
<IN>
SOFTWARE (SOF)
COMPUTERS AND INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (CPR)
</IN>
<LP>
   International Business Machines Corp. of Armonk, N.Y.,
said it will offer six software programs at no charge and
rebates to customers buying selected IBM Personal System/2(A)
models through Jan. 15.
   In addition, IBM will offer rebates on selected IBM
desktop printers to purchasers of qualified PS/2(A) systems.
Quick credit and deferred payments are also available, it
said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   IBM said it is offering the six software packages, which
it values at more than $600, to customers purchasing IBM's
PS/2 models 25 through 65. Customers buying the PS/2 Model
30-286, Model 50Z or Model 60 and an IBM operating system
will receive a $150 rebate; those buying PS/2 Models 55SX or
65SX and an operating system receive $300. Finally, customers
who purchase a qualifying PS/2 receive a rebate of $75 on an
IBM pro-printer and the LaserPrinter E, and $150 on the
10-page-per-minute LaserPrinter.
</TEXT>
